\begin_layout Section
Summary 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The examiner's report on the viva conducted on 2023-03-06 highlighted considerab
le shortcomings in how the thesis contents were organised.
 The report recommended a cautious definition of the scope of the thesis
 particularly in relation to how aspirational consumption had been defined
 in the thesis.
 The comments asked for a clearer connection with the literature on conventional
 views of aspirational consumption as visible consumption.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Thesis Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Organisation-related Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A preface and an epilogue have been added to the thesis in order to better
 motivate the topic and to provide a thread connecting the three chapters.
 The abstract as well as parts of the chapters have been changed to align
 with this thread.
 As suggested in the viva examination, the third chapter has been rewritten
 substantially.
 The re-organisation of the chapters has also resulted in making the theoretical
 chapter as the first chapter - which now discusses the theoretical concerns
 with the view of status consumption used in the thesis.
 Following is a summary of changes that are applicable to the thesis overall.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
A preface has been added to highlight the particular notion of status consumptio
n - highlighting key results from the empirical chapter while discussing
 the research question in more concrete terms.
 The problems with definition of status consumption are detailed in both
 the preface and the theoretical chapter - which now is the first chapter
 in the thesis.
 As suggested in the examiners' report, this first theoretical chapter also
 discusses real-life problems that the model in the chapter attempts to
 address.
 The scope of the specific view of status consumption has also been detailed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The introduction section from all the chapters has been reduced.
 Much of the content to motivate the thread has now been moved to a Preface.
 The Literature Survey sections have also been streamlined to address the
 specific problem explored by each chapter.
 The contribution of the chapter to the existing literature has also been
 highlighted (PENDING: evaluation of the extent to which litsurvey highlights
 contribution).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The first chapter which starts the discussion on status consumption is now
 a theoretical chapter.
 The empirical chapters are presented subsequently as instances of status-relate
d consumption in sub-Saharan Africa.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The discussion of social determinants takes more inputs from sociology literatur
e.
 A commentary on social determinants has now been replaced with specific
 social factors such as occupational categories, parental educational background
 and local wealth in the region.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
An epilogue now summarises the findings from the three chapters and discusses
 conclusions pertaining to the research question detailed in the preface.
\end_layout

